Speaking to TshisaLIVE just before the hotly-anticipated show, which has the entire nation excited, Cassper said that he was confident about filling the stadium to capacity."People generally wait for the last minute to buy tickets, so we're very confident that we will sell out," the rapper said.Cassper added that he's had sleepless nights in the lead up to the big day.The rapper has promised fans one helluva show with a world class stage and production. Cassper has also roped in his pals Nasty C, Babes Wodumo, Nadia Nakai and Euphonik to give fans a show to remember."I want kids to be inspired. There's always bad stuff being written and that stuff is depressing. It's not a conducive environment for young minds. They need to hear the good stories so they can be inspired to change the world."